<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<!-- Widgets increment: metadata for the Prüfung widget
     (PruefungWidgetProvider.java), referenced from the <receiver>
     meta-data in AndroidManifest.xml.

     minWidth/minHeight: sized for a nominal 3-cell-wide, 1-cell-tall
     placement. The standard cell-size formula ((70 × n) − 30 dp) gives
     180dp × 40dp for 3×1, but 40dp was already tight for three stacked
     text lines and got bumped to 64dp (see git history for the original
     3-line reasoning). Progress bar polish (0.40.0) adds a fourth row (the
     6dp bar plus its own top margin) between line1 and the two remaining
     text lines, so minHeight is bumped again here, to 84dp, using the same
     "give every row room, real launcher grids tend to be a bit more
     generous than the strict formula anyway" reasoning — still a judgment
     call, not a spec number, and still untested against a real launcher
     (no Android SDK/emulator available in this environment; see the
     increment's own "CI will prove" list).

     updatePeriodMillis: 6 hours. The widget's whole display is a 1:1
     calendar slide (m3: readyDayEpochMs slid forward by however many whole
     calendar days have passed since generatedDayEpochMs — see
     PruefungWidgetProvider.updateOne) off data that itself only changes
     when Deepak logs a sprint or edits the exam/topics — none of which need
     a redraw faster than a few times a day just to keep "today" current;
     refreshWidgets() (src/native/widgets.ts) already pushes an immediate
     redraw the moment any of that actually changes.

     previewImage intentionally omitted (increment brief: "acceptable;
     note it") — the widget picker falls back to rendering the
     initialLayout itself when none is set, which is why widget_pruefung.xml
     carries static placeholder text (m1) rather than empty TextViews: that
     placeholder IS the picker preview.

     android:description (m1, API 31+): a one-line summary shown under
     android:label in the picker on Android 12+; silently ignored on older
     API levels (this app's minSdk is 23), so no compatibility branch is
     needed for it. -->
<appwidget-provider xmlns:android="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res/android"
    android:minWidth="180dp"
    android:minHeight="84dp"
    android:updatePeriodMillis="21600000"
    android:initialLayout="@layout/widget_pruefung"
    android:description="@string/widget_pruefung_description"
    android:resizeMode="horizontal|vertical"
    android:widgetCategory="home_screen" />
